HEADWORD: Prenunciation
<hw>Pre*nun`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praenunciatio</ets>, fr. <ets>praenunciare</ets> to announce
beforehand. See <er>Pre-</er>, and <er>Announce</er>.]</ety> <def>The
act of announcing or proclaiming beforehand.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prenuncious</ent>⟦br⟧
